description.plain:
This song is Gretta Ray’s first big single, winning her both Triple J Unearthed High and the Vanda & Young songwriting competition in 2016.

The song follows Ray’s imagination as it wanders through her fantasies with her “latest muse”, a boy by whom she is deeply entranced.

body.plain:
This song is Gretta Ray’s first big single, winning her both Triple J Unearthed High and the Vanda & Young songwriting competition in 2016.

The song follows Ray’s imagination as it wanders through her fantasies with her “latest muse”, a boy by whom she is deeply entranced.

annotations:
Imagery such as this is symptomatic, you can call me a fanatic
 I’m an addict to what I can’t ever want

Amazing wordplay and rhyming here.
Imagining herself driving through the streets as depicted in the line above, is a symptom (symptomatic) that she is obsessed (fanatic) and hooked (addict) onto this fantasy of being with him.

Never joined at the hip, no
 I barely see you or know you but I feel like I do
 Now I’m invested, I am captivated and consumed
 Seems you’re my latest muse
They are not actually together but she feels so much for him.

That branched out of the thought of you and me
 It started out like a seed and then it grew like a tree
Her obsession for him grew from a small simple thought.

Whenever in your presence, I am present
 Imagination has me seated at your side

In saying that she is “seated” by his side, Gretta uses a double entendre, implying that, within her imagination, she is intently focused on him while also being literally seated at his side in the passenger seat.
I’ve been spaced out, in an absent dream
She has been daydreaming about this person she has feelings for.
